OL,3,CJersey nurseries struggle to operate
OL,4,Cwith lack of qualified staff
OL,6,FIn a joint statement, Jersey's
OL,7,FEducation Minister, Deputy Rob Ward,
OL,8,Fand Home Affairs Minister, Deputy Mary
OL,9,FLe Hegarat, say a policy to allow
OL,10,Fnurseries to employ qualified overseas
OL,11,Fstaff on work permits was introduced
OL,12,Fin 2023.
OL,14,FThey add that since then, 15 licences
OL,15,Fhave been given out across four
OL,16,Fnurseries.
OL,18,FRegulators also monitor staffing
OL,19,Flevels across the industry to make
OL,20,Fsure that all statutory requirements
OL,21,Fare being met.
